<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-06-22T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-06-22T13:00:00-05:00" n="217" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d217">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A5/106: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-06-22T19:00:00+01:00">June
                                        22, 1934—7 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received June 22—2:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>349. From Davis. Embassy’s telegram 344, June 22, noon. Bingham and I
                                feel that the program proposed by the British at the meeting of
                                experts yesterday is so unacceptable from our point of view that we
                                should tell the British we think it inadvisable to enter upon
                                technical discussions on such a basis. We will, however, cable later
                                our more considered views as to the course we should pursue.
                                [Davis.]</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bingham</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>